{"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "schema", "document", "Document"], "kwargs": {"page_content": "We denote the average (whether geometric, arithmetic, or exponentially weighted) gas usage of lane $\\ell$ at time $t$ as $G^N_{\\ell,t}$, and the cumulative average gas usage of all lanes as $G^N_{t}:=\\sum_{\\ell=1}^LG^N_{\\ell,t}$. The block space allocated to lane $\\ell$ at time $t+1$, denoted $B_{\\ell,t+1}$, can be calculated as:\n\n\\begin{aligned}\nB^*_{\\ell,t+1}=\\underbrace{\\frac{G^N_{\\ell,t}}{G^N_t}}_\\text{:=$p_{\\ell,t}$}B^*,\n\\end{aligned}\n\nNotice that this demand-based adjusting mechanism can also be combined with the proposed RBP-based adjusting mechanism, at the cost of having a more complicated model. \n\n## 4. Security considerations", "metadata": {}}}